root script to make plots on ntuples made by the "multiLepSearch" package

File description:
DataSample.txt : sample id, sample name, luminosity(in pb)

BGSample.txt : sample id, sample name, cross section(in pb), k-factor, filter efficiency, relative uncertainty
https://svnweb.cern.ch/trac/atlasoff/browser/PhysicsAnalysis/SUSYPhys/SUSYTools/trunk/data/susy_crosssections_13TeV.txt

SigSample.txt : sample id, sample name, cross section(in pb), BF, filter efficiency, relative uncertainty, mass of C1N2

https://svnweb.cern.ch/trac/atlasoff/browser/PhysicsAnalysis/SUSYPhys/SUSYTools/trunk/data/mc15_13TeV/MGPy8EG_A14N23LO_C1N2_WZ_XX_YY.txt
https://svnweb.cern.ch/trac/atlasoff/browser/PhysicsAnalysis/SUSYPhys/SUSYTools/trunk/data/mc15_13TeV/MGPy8EG_A14N23LO_C1N2_Slep_XX_YY.txt

skimming.C : generate ROOT files "skimming_SampleName.root" that separates into 6 channels. The root files are stored in the directory "skimming".
analysis1.C : make plots by using the input files "skimming.SampleName.root". The plots are saved in the directory "plot" in pdf format.
evt2l.C/.h : generated by ROOT via MakeClass
AtlasStyle.C/.h : Atlas style for plotting
AtlasLabels.C/.h : Atlas labels for plotting

unused:
rootlogon.C : needed when starting ROOT

Run:
use ROOT 6.04/02
root -l -b -q skimming.C
root -l -b -q analysis1.C

Possible problem:
If the ntuple format is updated, you should open the new format ntuple ROOT file, and regenerate the evt2l.C/.h via calling evt2l->MakeClass().
